  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 36b543b2fef67324c8ceabee10e6838c, type: 3}
  m_Name: Opening
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Name: Opening
  Dialogue:
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: A thousand years ago the Holy Martyr Petros (first of his name) willingly
      gave his life and was bathed in the sanctified light of God, proving the worth
      of mankind to their all-powerful creator.
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: "God looked down upon this one man\u2019s sacrifice and blessed the lands
      of Parva Mundi. The sins of mankind were instantly washed away, and the world
      was renewed in spirit, faith and generosity."
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: Generations have now passed and though the stories of the Martyr Petros
      are still told in the chapels and cathedrals of the lands, the many denominations
      that divided the faith bickered and argued over their version of the tale, often
      leading to conflict.
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: "The increase in reformations eventually forced the hand of Our Enlightened
      Saviour, Pontiff Bontiface VIII, to act against the heathens that he had proclaimed
      strayed far. He soon began excommunicating kings, sieging castles, seizing lands
      under the claim that \u201Call human creatures were subject to this rule\u201D."
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: Travelling the lands in a golden carriage protected by his most dedicated
      holy knights, Bontiface VIII proselytizing or burning villages in his wake.
      He ordered local clergymen drawn and quartered for condemning his actions as
      foretold in the Apocalypsis Tome.
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: One night he forcefully took a local woman for his own, ordering her family
      crucified for daring to resist the Will of God, then bedded her as her family
      screamed nearby.
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: 'When the villagers came to enact revenge on the Pontiff, his Holy Knights
      could not stop the tide as they dragged him to the granary and slowly pulverised
      his body beneath its great stone wheel, beginning with his toes. '
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: The screams of the Pontiff masked the sounds of demonic creatures crawling
      forth from the earth and dragging the nearby village to Hell.
  - Charecter: 0
    Text: Before anyone to act, it was too late. The End Times were upon them.
